abstract: Australian rules football players, all of whom punt as part of game, are finding success as punters on American college football teams; many have attended Melbourne academy Prokick, which specializes in training Australian rules players for that specific position in American game.
lead_paragraph: Michigan’s Blake O’Neill, whose muffed snap led to a last-second Wolverines loss to Michigan State, is one of a growing number of punters in the United States who developed their technique in Australian rules football.

headline.main: Australian Football Becomes a Punting Pipeline for the American Game
headline.print_headline: Kicking Feels Natural; the Helmet Doesn’t
